  "response_text": "A Black woman worker stands outdoors at an industrial energy facility under a blue sky. She faces forward, wearing a white hard hat with the red ExxonMobil name on the front, clear safety glasses, and a tan button-up work shirt with her name, “Regina,” embroidered on it. Long black braids fall over one shoulder, and a bright yellow safety device is clipped diagonally across her chest. Behind her are refinery-like metal structures, pipes, towers, and stacks. As she speaks, white subtitles appear near the bottom, including the message that the world needs ways to reduce carbon emissions, especially for heavy industry.\n\nThe scene changes to a white male worker standing in a busy port or shipping terminal. He wears a hard hat with goggles on it, a red high-visibility vest with reflective stripes over a dark shirt, orange earplugs hanging around his neck, and another yellow safety device clipped to his chest. Massive black crane structures rise behind him, with stacked multicolored shipping containers and the dark side of a large ship to his right. He faces forward and speaks calmly, standing squarely on the paved dock area.\n\nInside a dim, professional control room, a bearded man in a bright blue ExxonMobil work shirt faces forward. He has short dark hair, a salt-and-pepper beard, orange earplugs around his neck, and dark safety glasses hanging from the front of his shirt. Computer monitors and control panels glow softly around him in the background, suggesting an operations center.\n\nA woman in a large warehouse stands between long rows of huge silver metal coils, each coil stored upright on wooden supports. She wears a white hard hat, a red ExxonMobil shirt, and a reflective safety vest with yellow trim. The high ceiling is dark, with rows of overhead lights stretching into the distance. She faces forward while subtitles at the bottom refer to “carbon capture.”\n\nIn a laboratory, a woman with long dark hair and glasses stands in a navy ExxonMo